Description: Fragment of double handle of a Koan pottery transport amphora to moderate turn; one barrel only preserved. Clay near fine pink-buff; some mica; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 59. Name Argeios.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0097)
